From f2d59b3ca5a02beb167bbb5be34f9cfeac13e83a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 13:08:48 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 08/17] feat(concall): multi-file upload (PDF/PPTX/DOCX/TXT) +
 extraction v3 + SWIGGY fallback
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

User feedback after Aeroflex re-test + SWIGGY 'No data found':

A. MULTI-FILE UPLOAD
   New shared component ConcallUploadModal — drag-drop zone +
   multi-file list + paste-text textarea, all combinable. Each file
   shows individual parse status (queued / parsing / parsed / error)
   and char count. Used by both the India and US institutional
   reports (replaced the old paste-only modal in both).

   Server route /api/concall/parse accepts multipart upload, parses
   based on extension:
    - .txt / .md / .csv  →  utf-8 read
    - .pdf               →  pdf-parse (lazy import, ~50KB)
    - .docx              →  mammoth (lazy import, ~200KB)
    - .pptx              →  jszip + slide XML scrape (\<a:t\> tags)

   New deps: pdf-parse, mammoth, jszip. Dynamic import keeps the
   client bundle untouched; only the server function loads them
   when a file is uploaded. Shipped a pdf-parse.d.ts shim because
   the npm package ships JS only.

B. SWIGGY-STYLE BARE-SYMBOL FALLBACK
   Typing 'SWIGGY' (no .NS suffix) used to error with 'No data
   found' because the page only treated .NS / .BO / .BSE tickers
   as Indian. After EDGAR + FMP fail for a bare symbol, retry the
   India pipeline with ${ticker}.NS appended. Snapshot-build branch
   re-classifies to India when d.currency === 'INR' so SWIGGY,
   ZOMATO, and other recent IPOs pulled via fallback get the
   correct India-fundamental-only report.

C. EXTRACTION QUALITY V3 (Aeroflex re-test gaps)
   Top Quote #3 was 'Ashadham Reconstruction Rebuilding a facility
   for elderly need care…' — CSR section pollution. Top Quote #2
   was '46 Assembly Stations & 2 Robotic Welding Lines …' — capacity
   table dump.

    - stripBoilerplate now also chops out CSR Activities,
      Sustainability, Responsible Corporate, Ensuring Employee
      Well-Being, 'Why do X Matter?' sections, THANK YOU footers,
      Investor Relations Advisor blocks. SAT Foundation / Tribal
      Children / Annual Cricket Tournament / Bal Asha Trust strings
      are explicit triggers.
    - Sector KPI matching now has two tiers: prefer a clean prose
      sentence as evidence, fall back to 'keyword present in cleaned
      text but only inside tables' which still flips the KPI to ●
      with value 'mentioned in concall (P&L table)'. Fixes the
      Aeroflex EBITDA Margin gap (the deck only had 'EBITDA Margin#
      23.86%' in P&L tables — table-noise filter rejected the
      sentence but the KPI was real).
    - 6 new topical mentions: dividend, subsidiary, geographic_mix,
      capacity, rd_pipeline, customer_wins. Fixes Aeroflex misses
      on dividend declaration, Hyd-Air subsidiary growth, Domestic
      vs Export geo mix, R&D pipeline, capacity utilization.
    - 11 new positive tone phrases: well positioned, sustained
      momentum, growth opportunity, operational excellence, landmark
      milestone, long-term growth drivers, resilient business,
      dividend declared, investment in capability, successful entry,
      debt-free balance sheet, book-to-bill, global customer base.
    - Topic patterns tightened: each topic regex must now match a
      complete sentence with verbs, not a span.

Type-check passes (added pdf-parse.d.ts shim).

